What is difference between path and classpath variables?
A.  Path variable is used to set the path for all Java software tools like javac.exe, java.exe, javadoc.exe, and so on.
    Classpath variable is used to set the path for java classes.


What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
A.in an interface you can only declare non static methods and can implement only if static
in abstract class you can only declare and not implement abstract methods you can only implement non abstract or non static methods


Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
A.no you cannot make an object from an interface or an abstract class you can only do that through a concrete class after extending the methods.

what is Access Specifier?
A.Access specifiers are keywords in object-oriented languages that set the accessibility of classes, methods, and other members.


What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
A.OOP is Object Oriented Programming a method used for designing a program using classes and objects
    its features are
    Abstraction-Likewise in Object-oriented programming, abstraction is a process of hiding the implementation details from the user,
                only the functionality will be provided
    Inheritance- Inheritance can be defined as the process where one class acquires
                 the properties (methods and fields) of another.
    Encapsulation- It is used for data hiding
    Polymorphism-  Polymorphism in Java can be defined as the ability of an object to take many forms.

What is Java Package and which package is imported by default?
