Does java support multiple inheritance, explain why or why not?
A.multiple inheritance is not supported in java for classes and also for interfaces
    because the jvm can create only one object at a time

What is method overloading and when it happens?
A.f a class has multiple methods having same name but different in parameters,
    it is known as Method Overloading
    happens during compile time


Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it.
A-An exception is an unwanted or unexpected event, which occurs during the execution of a program
    can be handled using try catch

What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
A.In the Java programming language, the keyword static means that the particular member belongs to a type itself,
    rather than to an instance of that type.
    a variable is declared static when it is shared among all objects at the class level
    when a method is declared static it can be called directly without object creation


What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
A.Final keyword is a non-access specifier that is used to restrict a class, variable, and method
If we initialize a variable with the final keyword, then we cannot modify its value.
    If we declare a method as final, then it cannot be overridden by any subclasses.

What is final, finally and finalize?
A.FINAL keyword is a non-access specifier that is used to restrict a class, variable, and method
    In Java, FINALLY is a block used to place important code that will be executed whether or not an exception is handled.
    FINALIZE is the method of Object class. This method is called just before an object is garbage collected


What is a constructor ?
A.A constructor in Java is a special method that is used to initialize objects

Can we have multiple constructors in a class?
A.yes you can have a multiple constructors but with different parameters

If we don't have a constructor declared, what is called during the object creation?
A.default constructor is called

What is "this" keyword in java ?
A.this  refers to the current object of a method or a constructor.

What is "super" keyword in java? How many possible way can you use?
A.The super keyword in Java is a reference variable which is used to refer immediate parent class object
    If we have variable with same name in parent and child class,
    then we need to use super keyword to access parent class variable.

    If we have any method with same name in parent and child class,
    then we need to use super keyword to access parent class method.

    Super keyword can be used to call the parent class constructor.
    Using super we can call default or parameterized keyword.

What is JVM stand for ?
A-Java Virtual Machine

Is JVM platform independent?
A-The JVM is not platform independent.

What version of java are you using?
